node.text: Incredible is the only way to describe the new @HP OMEN X 65 Emperium gaming monitor premiered at #CES2019. With an industry-first NVIDIA ® G-SYNC deployment in a 65 inch screen, its 4K UHD resolution and 144hz refresh rate deliver silky smooth motion gameplay. Also getting a refresh is the Omen Obelisk with its pair of new M.2 SSD slots for max expandability and the Omen 15 gaming laptop, now sporting an NVIDIA® RTX 2070 GPU with MaxQ construction. Look into the future of #pcgaming with @OMENbyHP today.

node.title: HP OMEN came to play at CES 2019

node.text: If you’ve been waiting to use a keyboard and mouse for ultimate control and precision on your couch or desktop gaming, the long wait is up. @Razer brought their game-changing Turret to #CES2019. The world’s first wireless keyboard and mouse designed for @Xbox One, it boasts a lap-friendly ergonomic design, a mechanical keyboard with great tactile feel, as well as Razer Chroma™ lighting that syncs with #Xbox Dynamic Lighting to signal what’s happening in the game on the keyboard. Still game on a PC? Turret's got your back, it's plug and play with all #Windows10 PCs. See how the new Razer Turret can take your play to the next level today.

node.title: Razer’s cutting edge Turret at CES 2019

node.text: Go inside @lenovolegion’s amazing experience at #CES2019. They brought their new C730 and liquid-cooled T730 desktops and Y740 laptop. Both offer up to the latest 9th Gen Intel ® CORE™ K processors and NVIDIA ® GeForce RTX GPUs. Also new is a 27” 240hz QHD display, mechanical keyboard, and weighted gaming mouse. @lenovo

node.title: Lenovo Legion Gaming’s amazing CES 2019 experience
